    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\n**9 files to touch** across 5 crates, following the exact same patterns used by `uv cache size`:\n\n### New file\n- **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — Core implementation: iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, calls `diskus::DiskUsage` on each bucket's `PathBuf`, formats results in aligned columns with a separator line and total. Handles `--human` via the existing `human_readable_bytes` utility.\n\n### Modified files\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` preview feature flag (`\"cache-stats\"`) in 3 places (enum, `as_str`, `FromStr`).\n2. **`crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs`** — Add a `pub fn label(self) -> &'static str` method to `CacheBucket` returning short names (`\"wheels\"`, `\"sdists\"`, `\"flat-index\"`, etc.) for display.\n3. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum and a `StatsArgs` struct with the identical `--human`/`-H` flag as `SizeArgs`.\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`.\n5. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(...)`.\n6. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter helper.\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` with the same `test-python` + `test-pypi` feature gates as `cache_size`.\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — 3 integration tests: empty cache, raw bytes with packages, `--human` with packages.\n\n### Sample output\n```\nwheels         1.2GiB\nsdists         345.0MiB\nflat-index     12.3KiB\ngit            0B\ninterpreter    4.5KiB\nsimple         678.0MiB\narchive        234.0MiB\nbuilds         0B\nenvironments   56.7MiB\nbinaries       89.0MiB\n-----------------------\ntotal          2.6GiB\n```",
